TopicTitle: First flyby of the moon in RSS/RO!!!

Articles.Content:
Feel like a noob again, and i love it!!!

http://s29.postimg.org/4vz57d5ev/screenshot1.png

used an apollo style CSM, and an apollo-ish launcher, with only third stage built to IRL specs.
Got a picture of the daytime side, that one is a touch too dark to make out.
Nice job! I am trying RSS myself and I'm having a very hard time. It's good to see other people are making progress!
I only see blackness plus stars in that image. There might be a slight outline of an engine?

I only see blackness plus stars in that image. There might be a slight outline of an engine?

I'm guessing he's doing a free return which for me at least always puts me on the dark side of the Mun at periapsis

ill get a better picture, as well as my new updated CSM and Launcher, an SLS-esque launcher.
